<plot>Sally Phibbs finds out that if she tells one more lie, she will die instantly and go straight to Hell. Without the ability to lie, her life falls apart. Once she has alienated everyone in her life by telling them the truth at times when they would have preferred a lie, Sally realizes that lying isn't just something you do to protect yourself, but it's also an important part of protecting the ones you love from pain.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?422195</url></doc>
